OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F307A1773259872
OL,3,CStarmer's Mandelson misjudgment laid
OL,4,Cbare
OL,6,FIt's striking that in today's bundle
OL,7,Fof published documents is a note
OL,8,Fsaying that the then head of the
OL,9,Fforeign office Philip Barton and the
OL,10,Fnational security adviser Jonathan
OL,11,FPowell both had reservations about the
OL,12,Fappointment.
OL,14,FGiven their respect jobs, you would
OL,15,Fhave expected the PM to listen to
OL,16,Fthem. After all they were paid to know
OL,17,Fwhat's in UK's diplomatic interests.
OL,19,FStarmer, and McSweeney, thought they
OL,20,Fknew better.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G5/6
